TY  - JOUR
T1  - Consumers' Evaluation of New Products: Learning from Self and Others
AU  - McFadden, Daniel L.
AU  - Train, Kenneth E.
Y1  - 1996/08/01
PY  - 1996
DA  - 1996/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/262038
DO  - 10.1086/262038
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 683
EP  - 703
VL  - 104
IS  - 4
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - When offered a new product whose attributes are unknown, customers can determine whether they like the product by trying it themselves or can wait to observe the experience of other customers who try the product. We specify a rational decision process and investigate the implications of learning from others on the sales of new products and the impact of advertising.
AB  - When offered a new product whose attributes are unknown, customers can determine whether they like the product by trying it themselves or can wait to observe the experience of other customers who try the product. We specify a rational decision process and investigate the implications of learning from others on the sales of new products and the impact of advertising.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/262038
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/262038
Y2  - 2024/03/22
